Any Major Ensemble (100-level) course can go here.

Each Music major enrolled in at least 6 units of music courses should include a performance ensemble each quarter in order to qualify for applied study of voice or instruments. See current catalog for Major Ensemble at 100-level courses.

Any Free Elective course can go here.

Majors must demonstrate piano proficiency as part of the mid-point evaluation. Any piano classes needed before the piano proficiency examination will count as free electives. Completion of MU263 with a C- or better represents the fulfillment of the piano proficiency examination.

One course from each of the following GE areas must be completed: A1, A2, A3, B1, B2, Upper-Division B, C1, C2, Lower-Division C, Upper-Division C, D1, Upper-Division D, Lower-Division E, Lower-Division F, and GE Elective. Upper-Division B, Upper-Division C, and Upper-Division D should be taken only after Junior standing is reached (90 units). Refer to the online catalog for GE course selection, United States Cultural Pluralism (USCP), and Graduation Writing Requirement (GWR). The USCP requirement can be satisfied by some (but not all) courses within GE categories: Upper-Division B, C1, Upper-Division C, D1, Upper-Division D, or E.
